HEADWORD: Imperturbable
<hw>Im`per*turb"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>imperturbabilis</ets>; pref. <ets>im-</ets> not +
<ets>perturbare</ets> to disturb: cf. F. <ets>imperturbable</ets>. See
<er>Perture</er>.]</ety> <def>Incapable of being disturbed or
disconcerted; <as>as, <ex>imperturbable</ex> gravity</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

